{"name":"64ad47709904d55e4ea5","layouts":[{"id":0,"position":{"height":434.2857142857144,"width":362.8571428571429,"x":2.8571428571428568,"y":0,"z":3000,"tabOrder":0}}],"singleVisual":{"visualType":"textbox","drillFilterOtherVisuals":true,"objects":{"general":[{"properties":{"paragraphs":[{"textRuns":[{"value":"The effect of Queensland COVID-19 travel restrictions on \"Other Theft\" were immediate and pronounced. ","textStyle":{"fontWeight":"bold","fontSize":"12pt","color":"#063652"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"However, the travel restrictions did not address the underlying causes, and theft has returned to pre-COVID-19 levels.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":""}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"Compared to pre-COVID-19 levels, Northern and Central Queensland have seen the highest increase in Theft volumes, with the Northern region seeing a increase of +646 incidents.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":""}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":""}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"While the immediate drop in reported theft is consistent with the expected effect of travel restrictions, it's also possible that the re-allocation of Queensland Police Service resources to enforcing new restrictions may have reduced the number of completed investigations."}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":""}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"ABS defines 'Other theft' as illegally taking of another person's property with intention but without the use or threat of force ","textStyle":{"color":"#333333"}},{"value":"[1]","textStyle":{"color":"#333333","lineHeight":"0","position":"relative","verticalAlign":"baseline","scriptType":"super","top":"-0.25em"},"url":"https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/classifications/australian-and-new-zealand-standard-offence-classification-anzsoc/2023/07/079"}]}]}}]},"vcObjects":{"dropShadow":[{"properties":{"show":{"expr":{"Literal":{"Value":"false"}}}}}],"background":[{"properties":{"show":{"expr":{"Literal":{"Value":"false"}}}}}]}},"parentGroupName":"da88f7d6d00ced178503"}
